I"?<p>Cablegram 397 LONDON, 10 June 1940, 7.04 p.m.</p>

<p>MOST IMMEDIATE FOR THE PRIME MINISTER</p>

<p>Press report Mussolini in speech this afternoon stated declarations of war against the United Kingdom and France had been handed to the British and French Ambassadors. [1] No official confirmation yet received. [2]</p>

<p>BRUCE</p>

<p>_</p>

<p>1 Sir Percy Loraine and Andre Francois-Poncet.</p>

<p>2 This information was also received in U.K. Dominions Secretary’s cablegram C37 dispatched at 7.05 p.m. on 10 June 1940 (on file AA:</p>

<p>A1608, M41/1/1). The Commonwealth Government had previously been warned that war was possible within 48 hours in U.K. Dominions Secretary’s cablegram D241, dispatched at 4.20 a.m. on 9 June 1940 (on file AA: A1608, H41/1/4, ii).</p>

<p>_</p>

<p><em>[FA: A3195, 1.4081]</em></p>
